<para>
  <classname>PerimeterDisplay</classname> draws the outline of a
  &mesh;, <foreignphrase>i.e</foreignphrase>, it draws edges which
  are contained in only one element.  Like all &mesh; display
  methods, it can be drawn at the Mesh edge's <link
  linkend="Output-Position-original">original</link> positions,
  their <link linkend="Output-Position-actual">actual</link>
  displaced positions, or at <link
  linkend="Output-Position-enhanced">enhanced</link> positions.
</para>
<para>
  The <varname>width</varname> is in units of the screen pixel size.
</para>
<para>
  Compare with <xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-MicrostructurePerimeterDisplay"/>, which
  displays the rectangular perimeter of a &micro;, always at the
  undisplaced postions.
</para>
<note>
  <para>
    This ought to take empty elements into account.  It does not.
  </para>
</note>

